(44, 10, 14, 2, 10, 11, 11, 'Not so', 'Obedience and Rejection Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of refusal to obey divine commands. In both passages, the phrase ''Not so'' indicates a rejection of what is being asked, whether it is Peter''s reluctance to eat unclean food or the men being told to serve the Lord.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
