(44, 10, 15, 46, 10, 25, 25, 'What God hath cleansed', 'Cleansing and Eating', 'This connection highlights the theme of what God has cleansed being acceptable to eat. Both passages emphasize the idea that certain foods, previously considered common or unclean, are now permissible for consumption.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 15, 40, 15, 11, 11, 'What God hath cleansed', 'Defilement and Cleansing Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of what is considered clean or unclean. Both passages emphasize that external factors do not determine defilement, but rather internal actions and God''s declarations.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 15, 56, 1, 15, 15, 'What God hath cleansed', 'Purity and Defilement Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of purity and defilement. Both passages emphasize that what God has cleansed should not be considered impure, and that purity is a matter of the mind and conscience.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
